  "code": "%% Circuit Breaker Pattern - Fault Tolerance\n%% Version: 1.0.0\n%% Date: 2025-10-27\n%% Description: Circuit breaker pattern for webhook delivery and external service calls\n\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Closed: Initial State\n\n    Closed --> Open: Failure Threshold Exceeded<br/>(5 failures in 60s)\n    Closed --> Closed: Successful Request<br/>(Reset failure count)\n    Closed --> Closed: Failed Request<br/>(Increment failure count)\n\n    Open --> HalfOpen: Timeout Elapsed<br/>(30s wait period)\n    Open --> Open: Request Attempted<br/>(Fail fast, don't call service)\n\n    HalfOpen --> Closed: Test Request Successful<br/>(Reset circuit)\n    HalfOpen --> Open: Test Request Failed<br/>(Back to open state)\n    HalfOpen --> HalfOpen: Waiting for Test<br/>(Limited requests allowed)\n\n    note right of Closed\n        CLOSED STATE\n        - All requests flow through\n        - Monitor failure rate\n        - Track response times\n        - Increment error counter\n    end note\n\n    note right of Open\n        OPEN STATE\n        - Block all requests\n        - Return cached response\n        - Or return error immediately\n        - Wait for timeout period\n        - Log all blocked attempts\n    end note\n\n    note right of HalfOpen\n        HALF-OPEN STATE\n        - Allow test requests\n        - Limited throughput\n        - Monitor success rate\n        - Quick transition decision\n    end note\n",
  "content_size": 1387,
  "collected_at": "2026-02-06T14:06:18.048847",
  "compilation_status": "success",
